{"talk":{"id":2723,"name":"Katie Bouman: How to take a picture of a black hole","description":"At the heart of the Milky Way, there's a supermassive black hole that feeds off a spinning disk of hot gas, sucking up anything that ventures too close -- even light. We can't see it, but its event horizon casts a shadow, and an image of that shadow could help answer some important questions about the universe. Scientists used to think that making such an image would require a telescope the size of Earth -- until Katie Bouman and a team of astronomers came up with a clever alternative. Bouman explains how we can take a picture of the ultimate dark using the Event Horizon Telescope.","slug":"katie_bouman_how_to_take_a_picture_of_a_black_hole","recorded_at":"2016-11-19 00:00:00","published_at":"2017-04-04 15:10:25","updated_at":"2021-04-09 19:15:48","viewed_count":2077260,"emailed_count":0,"event":{"id":318,"name":"TEDxBeaconStreet"},"images":[{"image":{"size":"113x85","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/a0cc9a109510c2e6ba0148ca3350eb4c3d0a4952_113x85.jpg"}},{"image":{"size":"240x180","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/a0cc9a109510c2e6ba0148ca3350eb4c3d0a4952_240x180.jpg"}},{"image":{"size":"615x461","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/a0cc9a109510c2e6ba0148ca3350eb4c3d0a4952_615x461.jpg"}},{"image":{"size":"2400x1800","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/a0cc9a109510c2e6ba0148ca3350eb4c3d0a4952_2400x1800.jpg"}}],"image_16x9":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/bb720ff9ead8d6ca764da9aff093bf27b819a72e_2880x1620.jpg","media":{"internal":{"64k":{"uri":"https:\/\/download.ted.com\/talks\/KatieBouman_2016X-64k.mp4?apikey=c692baa7dafbf74e4fbde1ac88b44cafc96cfe7a","filesize_bytes":6397012,"mime_type":"video\/mp4"},"180k":{"uri":"https:\/\/download.ted.com\/talks\/KatieBouman_2016X-180k.mp4?apikey=c692baa7dafbf74e4fbde1ac88b44cafc96cfe7a","filesize_bytes":17726192,"mime_type":"video\/mp4"},"320k":{"uri":"https:\/\/download.ted.com\/talks\/Kati